          "notes": "Module has exceptional narrative integrity, concept accuracy, and pedagogical design with compelling opening scenarios, clear learning progression, and rigorous quiz/test items. However, D5 (Applied Outcome) is the critical weakness: labs depend on AI backend API that has offline fallback but provide limited scaffolding for judgment development, and executability is compromised by backend dependency without clear success criteria or validated learning outcomes.",
          "topIssue": "Lab executability is problematic: all four labs depend on API calls with no guarantee of availability, fallback responses are generic, and there is no clear rubric for what constitutes lab completion beyond exchange count threshold (3 exchanges). Labs should either have offline-first design with worked examples, or robust API with clear success criteria and learner-facing feedback on judgment quality, not just conversation count.",
